_0 is 9 times 10

00:37:56.800 --> 00:37:57.469
to the 9^(th).
 

00:37:57.469 --> 00:37:58.690
This is some number.
 

00:37:58.690 --> 00:38:02.773
Maybe 40 million,
so one coulomb gets 40 million

00:38:02.773 --> 00:38:03.469
lines.
 

00:38:03.469 --> 00:38:04.489
Don't quote the 40 million.
 

00:38:04.489 --> 00:38:05.869
It's whatever this thing is.
 

00:38:05.869 --> 00:38:07.030
I don't know what it is.
 

00:38:07.030 --> 00:38:08.679
It's a definite number.
 

00:38:08.679 --> 00:38:11.420
Then, what's the nice thing?
 

00:38:11.420 --> 00:38:16.753
If you've got q coulombs
you will have q over

00:38:16.753 --> 00:38:20.250
ε_0
lines,

00:38:20.250 --> 00:38:24.353
and if you take a sphere of
radius r you'll get 1

00:38:24.353 --> 00:38:28.010
over 4Πr^(2)^( )as the
line density,

00:38:28.010 --> 00:38:32.929
namely lines per unit area,
but that is exactly equal to

00:38:32.929 --> 00:38:36.239
the strength of the electric
field.

00:38:36.239 --> 00:38:37.936
If you picked a different
number like 2 over

00:38:37.936 --> 00:38:40.461
ε_0 you
will always be measuring 2 times

00:38:40.461 --> 00:38:41.369
the electric field.
 

00:38:41.369 --> 00:38:43.971
The density will still convey
