00:52:59.360 --> 00:53:04.576
So 2a times i
times q is the dipole

00:53:04.576 --> 00:53:05.429
moment.
 

00:53:05.429 --> 00:53:10.112
So this means electric field is
parallel to the dipole moment

00:53:10.112 --> 00:53:13.000
and falls like 1 over
x^(3).

00:53:13.000 --> 00:53:16.539
That's the most important part
of the dipole.

00:53:16.539 --> 00:53:18.737
A single charge,
the field falls like 1 over

00:53:18.737 --> 00:53:21.139
x^(2) if you move a
distance x.

00:53:21.139 --> 00:53:24.755
A dipole will always fall like
a bigger power of x,

00:53:24.755 --> 00:53:28.307
because to go like 1 over
x^(2) you've got to have

00:53:28.307 --> 00:53:29.260
