that the distance between them

00:53:38.920 --> 00:53:39.530
is not 0.
 

00:53:39.530 --> 00:53:41.960
And the distance will appear in
the numerator,

00:53:41.960 --> 00:53:43.690
and that must be the
corresponding distance in the

00:53:43.690 --> 00:53:45.643
denominator,
because the formula should have

00:53:45.643 --> 00:53:46.610
the same dimensions.
 

00:53:46.610 --> 00:53:49.762
That's what turns the 1 over
x^(2) to 1 over

00:53:49.762 --> 00:53:50.710
